<section id="ancients">
  <h2>Ancients <small class="text-muted fs-5">pre-500 AD</small></h2>
  <p>Covering everything from Bronze Age chariot warfare through to the fall of the Western Roman Empire — Greeks, Romans, Celts, Egyptians and beyond.</p>
  <h3>Regularly Played</h3>
  <p><em>Not currently actively played at the club.</em></p>
  <h3>Also Played</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Art de la Guerre (ADLG)</li>
    <li>Warmaster Ancients</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<hr>

<section id="medieval">
  <h2>Medieval <small class="text-muted fs-5">500–1500</small></h2>
  <p>The age of knights, castles, and crusades — from the early Dark Ages through to the Wars of the Roses and the Hundred Years' War.</p>
  <h3>Regularly Played</h3>
  <p><em>Not currently actively played at the club.</em></p>
  <h3>Also Played</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Barons' War</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<hr>

<section id="pike-and-shotte">
  <h2>Pike &amp; Shotte <small class="text-muted fs-5">1500–1700</small></h2>
  <p>The era of the Renaissance, the English Civil War, and the Thirty Years' War — when gunpowder began to reshape the battlefield alongside pike blocks and cavalry.</p>
  <h3>Regularly Played</h3>
  <p><em>Not currently actively played at the club.</em></p>
  <h3>Also Played</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Maurice</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<hr>

<section id="gunpowder">
  <h2>Gunpowder Era <small class="text-muted fs-5">1700–1900</small></h2>
  <p>Covering the Napoleonic Wars, the American Civil War, and the colonial conflicts of the 19th century — an era of muskets, artillery, and colourful uniforms.</p>
  <h3>Regularly Played</h3>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <img src="/public/img/longstreet-small.png" alt="Longstreet Front Cover" class="img-fluid">
        <div class="caption">
          <p>A ruleset covering the American Civil War by Sam Mustafa. A campaign is currently running at the club using this ruleset.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <img src="/public/img/fire-and-fury-front-cover.jpg" alt="Fire and Fury Front Cover" class="img-fluid">
        <div class="caption">
          <p>Another popular American Civil War ruleset at the club. This ruleset has stood the test of time and has a loyal following.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <h3>Also Played</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>LaSalle 2</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<hr>

<section id="ww1">
  <h2>WW1 <small class="text-muted fs-5">1914–1918</small></h2>
  <p>The Great War — trench warfare, the Western Front, and the dawn of modern industrial conflict.</p>
  <p><em>Not currently actively played at the club — but always welcome!</em></p>
</section>

<hr>

<section id="ww2">
  <h2>WW2 <small class="text-muted fs-5">1939–1945</small></h2>
  <p>The most popular period at the club. From North Africa to Normandy, there are several strong rulesets to choose from and plenty of opponents to find.</p>
  <h3>Regularly Played</h3>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <a href="/games/bolt-action/">
          <img src="/public/img/bolt-action-logo-small.png" alt="Bolt Action" class="img-fluid">
        </a>
        <div class="caption">
          <p>Bolt Action is a very popular World War 2 skirmish game and has been a regular at the club for many years, with most members familiar with the rules.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <a href="/games/flames-of-war/">
          <img src="/public/img/flames-of-war-logo-small.png" alt="Flames of War" class="img-fluid">
        </a>
        <div class="caption">
          <p>Another popular World War 2 ruleset at the club. Its popularity waxes and wanes but it has a good following at the club.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <h3>Also Played</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Eisenhower</li>
    <li>Blitzkrieg Commander</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<hr>

<section id="cold-war">
  <h2>Moderns &amp; Cold War <small class="text-muted fs-5">1945–present</small></h2>
  <p>The Cold War gone hot and beyond — ultra-modern armour, mechanised infantry, and the threat of nuclear escalation.</p>
  <h3>Regularly Played</h3>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <a href="/games/team-yankee/">
          <img src="/public/img/team-yankee-logo.png" alt="Team Yankee Logo" class="img-fluid">
        </a>
        <div class="caption">
          <p>Team Yankee is set during a mid-1980s Cold War gone hot scenario. Made by Battlefront, the makers of Flames of War — if you know one, you'll pick up the other easily.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr>

